data.content:
Here are the **three EF Core 10 breaking changes** that affect your code and how to fix each:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — Now accepts a regular lambda

Expression tree construction is no longer needed. Replace the entire block:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full path

Two changes hit you:
- **Duplicate property names** (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) get a numeric suffix appended.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` → column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate rename migrations. **Fix:** pin old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types — preserve old column name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>().ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
```

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Add the `string logCommandText` parameter to every method:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logs (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

All other methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) received the same extra parameter — update them all.
